[31m-# decision-decomposition[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Decision structuring tools for high-uncertainty environments.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Purpose[m
[31m-Ambiguous situations stall decisions when variables, constraints, and failure modes remain implicit.  [m
[31m-This repository provides methods to convert unclear problem statements into explicit, auditable decision structures.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Method[m
[31m-Input situations are decomposed into:[m
[31m-- Variables (controllable and observed)[m
[31m-- Constraints[m
[31m-- Invariants[m
[31m-- Failure modes[m
[31m-[m
[31m-The result is a structured representation suitable for analysis, comparison, and downstream decision processes.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Inputs[m
[31m-- Short text descriptions[m
[31m-- YAML or JSON problem statements[m
[31m-- Non-sensitive, open-domain scenarios only[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Outputs[m
[31m-- Structured decision models[m
[31m-- Constraint and dependency graphs[m
[31m-- Enumerated invariants and failure modes[m
[31m-- Logged metrics[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Metrics[m
[31m-- Time-to-clarity (from input to stable structure)[m
[31m-- Variable completeness[m
[31m-- Constraint density[m
[31m-- Failure-mode coverage[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Metrics are recorded for reproducibility and comparison.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Scope[m
[31m-This repository is intentionally limited to neutral and public examples.  [m
[31m-It demonstrates method and structure, not domain-specific conclusions.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Design principles[m
[31m-- Explicit structure over narrative[m
[31m-- Logs over prose[m
[31m-- Reproducibility over explanation[m
[31m-- Auditability over persuasion[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Evaluation[m
[31m-Baseline comparisons are included to show decision degradation when explicit structure is absent.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-The primary evaluation question is simple:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-What becomes clearer, faster, or more stable once the structure exists?[m
[31m-[m
